 Port Elizabeth - A 24-year-old alleged suspect will appear in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate's Court on Tuesday for the alleged murder of a 28-year-old male in Kwanoxolo on Saturday. "It is alleged that at about 23:15, Etienne Koopman and his friends were drinking in front of a house in Siyazama Street in Kwanoxolo when an argument broke out between Koopman and the suspect," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "Koopman was stabbed thrice (in the back, eye and chin) and died on the scene. "The suspect then ran away." She said that on Sunday, SAPS Bethelsdorp members received information that the suspect was at a local hospital receiving treatment. "It is further alleged that he had sustained a stab wound to his head," Col Naidu said. "The suspect was arrested and detained on a charge of murder." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  